{
  "texts": [
    "• Negative-There is moderate or high-quality evidence indicating that the intervention is ineffective or harmful.",
    "• Equal-The interventions analysed were equally effective and safe.",
    "• Positive inconclusive-There is evidence suggesting effectiveness or safety, but it is of low quality or inconclusive, and the authors suggest that more research is needed.",
    "• Negative inconclusive-There is evidence of ineffectiveness or harm (evidence demonstrating that there was no effect or that the intervention was not safe) or authors urged against the intervention or comparison, or it is not recommended; however, the evidence is of low quality or inconclusive, or authors state that more research is needed.",
    "• Equal inconclusive-The interventions appear to be similarly effective and safe, but the evidence is of lower quality or inconclusive, and the authors suggest that more research is needed."
  ]
}